I agree with what you said in #2.  My point (unproven, untested, and
probably unprovable and untestable) is that descriptions of what
awakening is like are more likely to steer one away from awakening
than towards it.  Any descriptions will miss the mark, or be partial
at best.

The fact that you have said there is more than one way to describe it
somewhat illustrates this point.  The reason there are so many ways to
describe it is that not one of them is adequate in and of itself.  If
it could be perfectly described, and it the means for it's attainment
could be perfectly mapped out, everybody would have awakened by now.

